==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Isoclinic
<hw>I`so*clin"ic</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Iso-</ets> + Gr. <?/ to
incline.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to, or indicating, equality of
inclination or dip; having equal inclination or dip.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Isoclinal lines</b></col> <fld>(Magnetism)</fld>,
<cd>lines on the earth's surface connecting places at which a dipping
needle indicates the same inclination or dip.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Isocrymal</ent>⟦br⟧
